Always read PLAN.md in the project root before answering. It is the authoritative
spec — case, contract, architecture, data model, endpoints, RAG details, security
mapping, build phases, and the deviations log. Build against it.

Key rules for this project:
- Technical content (code, comments, commits, README) is written in English.
- Conventional Commits (feat:, fix:, docs:, refactor:, chore:, test:), imperative mood.
- Secrets live in .env only (gitignored). Never hardcode keys.
- Generation uses Anthropic Claude Sonnet. Embeddings use OpenAI text-embedding-3-small. Whisper runs locally via n8n.
- If a change deviates from PLAN.md, flag it and add it to the "Deviations from
  Inlämning 1" section so it can be motivated in the reflection.
- Do not write to ARBETSLOGG.md. That is the developer's own log, written in their own words.